_precipitations_','')\n    df['Community']=name.capitalize()\n    dfs.append(df)\nmp = pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)\n\n# Clean M or missing -> NaN, ensure numeric\nmonths = ['Jun','Jul','Aug']\nfor m in months:\n    mp[m] = pd.to_numeric(mp[m].replace('M', np.nan), errors='coerce')\n\n# compute month medians across all years and stations? Task: impute missing monthly precipitation values with each month's median over the available years.\n# Interpret as per station: median over available years for that station-month. But \"over the available years\" could mean across all stations. Gold chain said: For each precipitation station, impute missing June, July, and August values with month medians and compute 2020 through 2023 summer rainfall totals.\n# So compute per-station month median across years in that station, then fill.\n\nmp_sorted = mp.copy()\n# compute medians per Community and Month\nfor m in months:\n    med = mp_sorted.groupby('Community')[m].transform('median')\n    mp_sorted[m] = mp_sorted[m].fillna(med)\n\n# Filter years 2020-2023\nmp_recent = mp_sorted[mp_sorted['Year'].between(2020,2023)]\n# sum Jun+Jul+Aug as SummerTotal per station-year\nmp_recent['SummerTotal'] = mp_recent[['Jun','Jul','Aug']].sum(axis=1)\n# aggregate by Community across stations (here Community corresponds to dataset community names) sum of summer totals per year\ncity_totals = mp_recent.groupby(['Year','Community'])['SummerTotal'].sum().reset_index()\n# Now sum across communities to get total summer rainfall per year\nyearly_rainfall = city_totals.groupby('Year')['SummerTotal'].sum().reindex([2020,2021,2022,2023]).fillna(0)\n\n# Load precipitations_beaches_community mapping\nprecip_map_df = pd.read_csv(precip_map)\n# normalize community names\nprecip_map_df['Community'] = precip_map_df['Community'].str.strip()\n# Find which communities are Fresh\nfresh_communities = precip_map_df[precip_map_df['Beach Type'].str.contains('Fresh', case=False, na=False)]['Community'].unique()\n\n# Process water-body-testing files to compute exceedance rates for freshwater beaches per year\nexceed_rates = {}\nfor wf in water_files:\n    wdf = pd.read_csv(wf, parse_dates=['Sample Date'])\n    year = int(Path(wf).stem.split('-')[-1])\n    # filter to Year column 2020-2023 and Beach Type Description contains 'Fresh'\n    # The dataset has 'Beach Type Description' field; also has 'Community'. We'll filter by community being in fresh_communities\n    wdf_year = wdf[wdf['Year']==year]\n    # Filter to freshwater using community mapping\n    wdf_fresh = wdf_year[wdf_year['Community'].isin(fresh_communities)]\n    # Exceedance defined as Violation == 'Yes' or Indicator Level? Use Violation column\n    total = len(wdf_fresh)\n    exceed = len(wdf_fresh[wdf_fresh['Violation'].str.strip().str.lower()=='yes'])\n    rate = exceed/total if total>0 else None\n    exceed_rates[year]= {'total': total, 'exceed': exceed, 'rate': rate}\n\n# Build year-to-year increase/decrease sequences for rainfall totals and exceedance rates\n# rainfall sequence: compare 2020->2021, 2021->2022, 2022->2023 -> 'up' if increased, 'down' if decreased, 'same' if equal\nr_seq = []\nyears = [2020,2021,2022,2023]\nfor i in range(len(years)-1):\n    a = yearly_rainfall.loc[years[i]]\n    b = yearly_rainfall.loc[years[i+1]]\n    if b>a:\n        r_seq.append('up')\n    elif b<a:\n        r_seq.append('down')\n    else:\n        r_seq.append('same')\n\n# exceedance seq\ne_seq = []\nfor i in range(len(years)-1):\n    a = exceed_rates[years[i]]['rate']\n    b = exceed_rates[years[i+1]]['rate']\n    if a is None or b is None:\n        e_seq.append(None)\n    else:\n        if b>a:\n            e_seq.append('up')\n        elif b<a:\n            e_seq.append('down')\n        else:\n            e_seq.append('same')\n\nprint('yearly_rainfall:')\nprint(yearly_rainfall.to_dict())\nprint('rainfall_seq:', r_seq)\nprint('exceed_rates:', exceed_rates)\nprint('exceed_seq:', e_seq)\n\n# final comparison boolean\nmatch = (r_seq==e_seq)\nprint('match:', match)\n\n# For submission, output just boolean as string in [] and brief reasoning\nresult = match\nresult, r_seq, e_seq, yearly_rainfall.to_dict(), exceed_rates\n", "intent": "Compute summer rainfall totals per year 2020-2023 after imputing Jun-Jul-Aug per station medians, compute freshwater beach exceedance rates per year, derive year-to-year up/down sequences and compare them."}) [toolUseId=call_MnavDJ4FZRVzewaaUjuFzDEX]
